No News from The European Mars Probe - Beagle 2 after It Landed
( AFP in London on the first ) Spokesman Barratt of the Mars probe plan said that an American satellite wishes to collect signals from Beagle 2 after the satellite failed to get in touch with Beagle 2 . Now we can only place our hope on its mothership Mars Express .
Barratt said : " we have not achieved further information . "
He said : " we have now placed our hope on its mother ship Mars Express and we wish it could gather some information . "
The American Mars probe Odssey spaceship received no information from Beagle 2 yesterday which continues to look for life signs on Mars after it landed on Mars from Mars Express .
The Mars Odyssey spaceship was launched by NASA to enter the Mars orbit for another probe mission .
The European Space Administration located in Paris said that the man-made satellite Mars Express made by Europe has been sent to the polar orbit of the Mars and it will hopefully send back some signals .
Beagle 2 was scheduled to land on Mars on Christmas day , but its signals are still elusive .
Beagle 2 has become the first European spaceship that has landed on another planet after it departed from the mother ship Mars Express on December 19 .
During its 18-day mission , Beagle 2 plans to test the rocks , soil and modes of signal transmission gathered from the Mars to the investigate all the present life forms on Mars .
Scientists once boldly predicted that this British spaceship might be caught in craters .
The Pakistani President Musharraf Won The Vote of Confidence in Senate and Lower House
( AFP in Islamabad on first ) The Pakistani President Musharraf won the vote of confidence of Senate and Lower House today although the Islamic creed members abstained and the opposition parties boycotted . This victory ensures that Musharraf will maintain his rule until the year 2007 .
The Information Minister Rasheed told the correspondents of AFP : " Musharraf had won the majority votes of the parliament .
No parliament members voted against him . "
In the 342-seat lower house , 191 members voted for Musharraf ; the Islamic creed members abstained ; the opposition parties boycotted this vote of confidence which was under dispute .
Musharraff made a concession to the federation of 6 Islamic parties . He agreed to resign the post of the army commander-in-chief and at the same time dissolve the parliament . He would try his best to get approval from the supreme court within one month .
In the 100-seat upper house , 56 members voted to support Musharraf and 42 Islamic and opposition members either abstained or boycotted .
Musharraf came to power in a coup in October , 1999 and has refused to step down ever since .
The Burundi President : The Former Rebellious Army Shall Join The Military Leadership
( AFP in Bujumbura on the first ) Today Burundi President Ndayizeye delivered his New Year Day address to the whole nation . He said that the post-war joint chiefs of staff was to be set up by next week and its members would include the former rebellious army leaders .
The former rebellious army the " Forces for the Defense of Democracy " expresses its welcome , praising it as " an important step " towards the establishment of new armed forces .
President Ndayizeye delivered a television speech , saying that arrangements must be made by January 5 for the rebellious troops of the past 10 years . New military , 40 % of which would b e former rebellious army leaders , shall be set up by January 7. leadership shall be set up by January 7 .
Ndayizeye said : " the parties that have signed ( the November 2003 ceasefire ) agreement should complete their arrangement before January 5 for the station locations of troops . "
He also stated that the joint chiefs of staff including rebellious army leaders should be set up no later than January 7 .
This work is chiefly related to the " Forces for the Defense of Democracy " , the largest of the 6 rebellious military organizations that signed the truce .
The 7th rebellious organization " FNL " refused to sign the peace accord .
About 300,000 people have been killed in Burundi since the civil war broke out between the Hutu rebellious army and the Tutsi government army in 1993 .
China Has Detained 186 Tons of American Beef
( AFP in Beijing on the second ) China 's state-owned news media " Beijing Youth " reports today that the authorities have carried out a general check-up of the meat market due to fear of BSE and detained in Beijing 186 tons of American beef yesterday .
Beijing Youth points out that this batch of beef will be destroyed after being tested on the proposal of the Ministry of Agriculture .
Over 30 countries suspended their import of American beef last week . China is one of them .
All the beef-related products are prohibited except milk and other dairy products , leather and gelatin emulsion used in photography .
According to Beijing Youth , recently Beijing Agricultural Bureau has issued a series of decrees for prevention and supervision and has carried out a general market check-up .
So far no BSE case has been reported in China .
The above-mentioned detention of beef is the second such action in nearly a week . Some time ago the authorities found and detained 60 kg of beef on board an American cargo ship in Ningbo City of Zhejiang Province . The beef was produced by the state of Washington in the USA where BSE cases have been reported .
Although China imported 532 million USD worth of meat from America last year according to statistics of the Ministry of Commerce , the actual amount of beef import is still unclear .
From January to July last year , China imported 316 million USD worth of meat from the USA .
It Is Reported That North Korea Has Authorized The USA Delegation to Visit Yongbyon Nuclear Complex
( AFP in Washington on second ) According to USA Today , the Pyongyang authorities have authorized an American delegation whose members include top nuclear scientists to visit North Korea 's Yongbyon nuclear complex next week .
The delegation members have told USA Today that the Bush Administration has ratified the expected tour of North Korea by the American delegation from January 6 to 10 .
This will be the first foreign delegation to visit the disputable nuclear complex in North Korea since the UN inspectors were expelled by North Korea a year ago .
On the American Delegation are a Chinese expert from Stanford University , two foreign policy assistants from the Senate and a former official of the State Department who is responsible to deal with Pyongyang .
The nuclear expert of the delegation is Hecker who led the American Los Alamos National Laboratory , the very laboratory which the atom bomb was first developed , from 1985-1997 .
Before this North Korea notified the American Embassy in Beijing that the Pyongyang authorities are ready to attend the delayed second round of 6-party talks on the nuclear crisis on the Korean peninsula .
An American official points out this week that the Pyongyang authorities have made it clear that it will attend the 6-party talks to be held early this year .
No conclusion was reached in the first round of the 6-party talks held in Beijing last August . North Korea criticized the talks as " useless " .
The second round of the 6-party talks was originally scheduled to be held last December . It had to be postponed until early this year due to differences over what measures to take to solve the problems .
The Washington authorities want North Korea to give up its nuclear program unilaterally . However , the Pyongyang regime insists that the USA provide security guarantee that has legal binding power in return for its waiver of nuclear program .
The American Government Said That It Has Nothing to Do with The American Delegation to Visit North Korea
( AFP in Washington on second ) The American government indicates today that it has nothing to do with the two American delegations which are prepared to visit North Korea and wish to give rise to a diplomatic storm over Yongbyon nuclear complex .
At a time when China is urging the USA , North Korea , Japan , Russia and South Korea to return to negotiation table , a delegation consisting of American experts and scientists and another delegation made up of assistants from the American congress plan to visit North Korea .
The deputy spokesman of the USA State Department Ereli said that " we have nothing to do with this or these delegations and their programs which are said to visit North Korean . "
Ereli said : " I believe it should be made clear to all that these delegations and individuals do not represent the government . "
One of the delegations is headed by a senior Chinese expert from Stanford University and Hecker , former dean of Los Alamos Laboratory and its members include Pritchard , special envoy of the American State Department who held talks with North Korea last year .
According to USA Today , this delegation will visit Yongbyon nuclear plant . But one of its members told AFP that the tour to Yongbyon is still uncertain .
There might be changes after the extensive coverage of mass media . It is still uncertain whether or not this delegation will get permission to enter North Korea .
The other delegation is headed by Luse , the assistant of Chairman Richard Lugar of the Senate Foreign Relations Committee and Jannuzi , the assistant of the Democratic chief member Biden of the Senate Foreign Relations Committee .
The United States of America Is Waiting For Israel to Clarify Its Plan on Land Reclamation on Golan Heights
( AFP in Washington on second ) The American government indicates today that Israel has not given a satisfactory answer to the American demand for a clarification over its plan to extend its reclamation plan on Golan Heights .
The State Department said that Israel already gave a reply to USA on Wednesday ( 31st ) after the event was reported .
However , Israel 's reply cannot remove all the doubts of the USA over the issue .
The Deputy spokesman Ereli of the state Department said : " We have received a reply , bur it is not clear enough and we are still in doubt . "
He reiterates the government 's opposition to any new reclamation by Israel .
Ereli said : " We have already made it clear that we are opposed to any new reclamation which , we believe , is of no avail and should be stopped . "
According to mass media , Israel plans to establish 9 new reclamation districts in 1976 on its occupied Golan Heights from Syria and intends to promote the Israeli population from 10,500 to 15,000 within 3 years .
This occupation act was widely criticized by the Arab countries as illegitimate .
The Toyota Prius Sedan Wins The Title of North American Car of the Year
( AFP in Detroit on 4th ) The Toyota Prius has been elected by journalists as North American Car of the Year and the F-150 full-size pickup of Ford Motor Company took Truck of the Year honours .
Press , executive vice president in charge of sales , said : " This award does a lot to validate the hybrid powertrain vehicles . "
The power sources of the Prius redesigned for 2004 are gasoline and electricity . It was introduced in October last year and its price is 20,000 USD . The early marketing situation is better than the expected .
Last month Toyota Motors announced that it will promote the output of Prius by 31 % .
Press said that Toyota wishes that the successful introduction of new Prius could promote the sale of SUV , Highlander which also uses gas and electricity as power sources and which will be introduced later this year .
The new Highlander will debut at the North American International Auto Show in the coming days .
Today 's show is exclusively for mass media .
The redesigned F-150 truck of Ford Motors has won Truck of the Year .
According to Lyons , executive president of a sales department of Ford , F-150 is the best seller in the world . The F-150 for 2004 has been redesigned and it set a record sale figure in December last year , with 84,600 units sold .
Lyons said that Ford will continue its endeavor after the successful sale of F-150 and will achieve its goal of selling one million F-series trucks within this year .
Zambia Plans to Expel The British Writer Who Is Suspected of Insulting Its President
( AFP in Lusaka on 5th ) The Zambian Home Affairs Minister Shikapwasha said that Zambia has ordered the British writer Clark to leave the country in 24 hours because he was accused of insulting the Zambian President Mwanawasa in a column article on a private newspaper entitled Post .
Shikapwasha told a group of Mwanawasa 's supporters who marched to the Home Affairs Ministry to demand the renvoi of Clark that " Clark must leave in 24 hours .
I will announce to the whole country that we have taken actions . "
However , Clark said that he hasn 't received any notice when interviewed by AFP .
Clark said : " I don 't know anything about that the order of renvoi was issued . "
The permanent secretary of the Home Affairs Ministry Peter Mumba pointed out earlier that he has suggested to the Ministry that an order be issued to deport Clark .
Mumba said : " When a person insults the president of a country , he is as good as insulting the people he represents . He should go back to write about his own people . "
Clark has stayed in Zambia for many years and has married a Zambian woman movement activist .
The editor of Post M 'membe said that he personally would be willing to be responsible for the article and he urged the Zambian government to point the spearhead at him instead of Clark .
This is not the first time for Zambia to deport a foreigner who has insulted the president or a government leader .
Koizumi Pledged to Continue The Economic Reform
( AFP in Tokyo on 5th ) The Japanese Prime Minister Koizumi made the pledge at a news conference on the first working day after the new year holidays . He will continue the on-going economic reform . He said : " Although the economic situation is still hard , we are seeing signs of recovery at last . "
Koizumi stressed " I will adhere to reform policies and continue to promote reform .
The efforts to continue reform will enhance the economic recovery . "
Koizumi indicates that he will focus his attention on the examination and approval of privatization of postal service by the diet .
He said : " We can at last take actions on privatizing postal service . This is the mainstay of the economic reform . "
Koizumi added that he wishes to submit the bill about the plan to the diet early next year .
Koizumi promises to privatize the postal service with a total staff of 280,000 by 2007 .
The Japanese postal service is regarded as the world 's largest bank , for it manages 355,000 billion Japanese Yen ( 3,300 billion USD ) as deposits and insurance funds .
But this gigantic plan still faces strong opposition of the conservative diet members .
The plan originated from the time when Koizumi served as the Minister of Postal Service .
Analysts point out that Japanese economy is predicted to grow steadily by 2 % . But the Japanese public are still worried about cutting the salary and firing the employee mroe .
When many companies are conducting rectification to ensure profits , the unemployment rate in Japan is still above 5 % .
The USA Has Started to Take Photos And Fingerprints of Foreign Travelers Who Enter The Country
( AFP in Washington on 5th ) At a time when Singapore where the largest airport in Asia is located is for the airliners to be equipped with armed police to cope with terrorist threat , the USA has started today the new measure of taking photos and fingerprints of foreign travelers entering America .
The Washington authority tightens its screening of foreign travelers when worries over aviation security are rising all over the world . Over the past week the afore-mentioned worries have caused several flights into and out of America to be cancelled fo the time being .
The new measure of taking photos and fingerprints is only for those travelers who cannot enter USA without visas . Generally the number of such travelers is predicted to be 23 million this whole year .
The Homeland Security Department which is responsible for the implementation of the United States visitor and Immigrant Status Indicator Technology ( US-VISIT ) points out that 28 countries , mostly European nations , are exempt from the above procedures .
Immigration organization attack this plan as an infringement on citizens ' right of liberty and as a step towards a monitored society . The Secretary of Homeland Security Ridge argues hard in favor of the plan .
When interviewed by NBC , Ridge said " one of the priority responsibilities of any government is to ensure the border safety . We work out this plan just to fulfil this duty . I don 't think it is rash . Obviously nobody cares much about this practice which in fact takes no more than 15 seconds . "
By 2005 all the entrances by land , by sea or by air will be equipped with the photo- and fingerprint-taking devices .
All the American visas and passports will finally include photos and fingerprints " distinguishing marks biological identity " .
Before the above plan was implemented , the USA began to raise its alarm grade for terrorist attacks in December last year .
US And North Korea Are Unyielding in Their Positions . The 6-Party Talk Will Probably Be Postponed until The Middle of This Year .
( AFP in Seoul on 6th ) South Korea says today that another round of 6-party talk will perhaps be put off until the middle of this year due to the unyielding attitudes of North Korea and the USA .
The Foreign Minister of South Korea Yoon Young-kwan , who was attending a cabinet meeting at Blue House , told journalists : " I wish the talk to be preferably held in the first half of this year the latest . "
After turning down Pyongyang 's new proposal to exchange nuclear freezing for significant concessions and suggesting the necessity for the two parties to solve the big differences , Yoon Young-kwan delivered the above statement .
Yoon Young-kwan indicates that the time tables of the 6 participating countries exclude , as a matter of fact , the possibility of reopening the 6-party talk in January .
However , he provides no clue as to why the talk will probably be put off until June or even later .
Deputy Foreign Minister of Russia Losyukov attribute this to the unyielding attitudes of America and North Korea .
He took part in the first round of 6-party talks held in Beijing in August last year .
After having talks with senior Chinese officials yesterday , Losyukov told the Interfax News Agency that " the reason is the same as the past ; there is a lack of mutual trust ; the demands of the 2 parties are too harsh . "
After North Korea requested the US for the second time to promise major concessions before a new round of talks , Yoon Young-kwan puts forward the possibility of the talks to be delayed for a long time .
The American government accuses Pyongyang of setting preconditions for a new round of the 6-party talks .
The USA is trying to have North Korea promise to give up its nuclear program .
North Korea states that it is ready to freeze its nuclear facilities provided that the American Government lifts up its economic sanctions and restores its energy aid .
In the past North Korea also insisted that a non-aggression treaty be concluded with the USA .
The Summit Meeting of South Asia Came to Conclusion And The Relation between India And Pakistan Sees The Dawn Of Thawing
( AFP in Islamabad on 6th ) The south Asian summit closed today . During the meeting the two nuclear powers of India and Pakistan have had breakthrough talks . The participant countries have concluded a free trade agreement . All this is of epoch-making significance for south Asian regions .
Ms. Zia , Premier of Bengal , pointed out at the closing meeting of the 12th South Asian Association of Regional Cooperation ( SAARC ) Summit that " this summit is a watershed for strengthening south Asia regional cooperation . "
The Indian Premier Vajpayee and the Pakistani President Musharraf held a talk at the side of the conference hall , the first such talk since the nuclear crisis between the two countries in 2002 .
The hostility between the 2 powers of SAARC has been an obstacle for regional development . The leaders of the participant countries are greatly encouraged by the fact that the historic talk will obviously promote peace .
The military analyst of Pakistan Masood said to AFP : " I believe thare are clear changes on the positions of India and Pakistan . The two countries are marching towards peace process . "
When the premier of Pakistan Jamali formally announced the summit closed , he commended the summit on its efforts in fighting against terrorism and poverty and its agreement to set up a free trade region by 2006 .
He also said that the summit has " added new vigor to the regional cooperation . "
The state heads and foreign ministers of Bangladesh , Bhutan , India , Maldives , Nepal , Pakistan and Sri Lanka signed at the summit the South Asia Free Tread Agreement " SAFTA " , the Social Charter , the Anti-Poverty Plan , the Anti-Terrorism agreement and " Islamabad Declaration . "
Bush Commended NASA 's Mars Mission
( AFP in Washington on 6th ) American President Bush congratulated by phone the officials of NASA on their Mars mission today . He also praised them as saying that their success has healed the wound of the space shuttle Columbia .
White House spokesman McClellan told the media : " The president thanks NASA for its good team work and resourcefulness and also approves the great adventurism of Americans . "
Bush said that he shared the thrills when the Spirit robot sent back the first color picture of its landing place from the red planet .
McClellan said : " The president was as excited as the American public when we witnessed the dramatic scene .
Nevertheless , we know that this is but a glimpse of Mars by the Spirit . "
McClellan said : " Bush strongly supports space exploration . In the meanwhile he expresses his thanks to the NASA staff whose endeavor has resulted in the success and has enabled America to lead the world in space exploration and discovery . "
Kiharu Nakamura , The Great Japanese Geisha of No Equal of Her Time , Died in New York at The Age of 90
( AFP in Tokyo on 7th ) The Japanese publisher Soshisha announces that Kiharu Nakamura , who gave up her career as a Japanese geisha and has lived in America for nearly half a century died in her house in New York at the age of 90 on 5th .
Soshisha has published 10 books about Kiharu Nakamura including " The Memoir of a Tokyo-born Geisha " a best seller published in 1983 .
" The Memoir of a Tokyo-born Geisha " has been translated into 8 languages and adapted into a TV play and a stage play . The book depicted that Kiharu Nakamura was the only geisha who spoke English in the days before World War II .
French avant-garde artist Jean Cocteau , king of comedy Charlie Chaplin and US baseball star Babe Ruth were among foreign celebrities who were entertained by Nakamura when they visited Tokyo .
Soshisha said that Nakamura gave Jean Cocteau inspiration to write the poem " Geisha " .
Soshisha made an announcement that Kiharu Nakamura was born in a doctor 's family in a luxurious district of Tokyo . She became a geisha of the New Bridge Entertainment Area at the age of 16 despite the opposition of her parents .
After years of work as a geisha at New Bridge , Nakamura married a diplomat and soon afterwards they were divorced .
After the war , Nakamura returned to her geisha career . She immigrated into the USA in 1956 .
In US , while teaching traditional Japanese music and dance , Nakamura also served as a consultant for operas , including Madame Butterfly .
Nakamura has a son who is now a university professor of modern arts .
Vietname Airlines Initiated A New Route to Frankfurt of Germany
( AFP in Hanoi on 8th ) The Vietnamese Airlines has begun a twice-weekly service to Frankfurt , Germany . This is the second destination of Vietname Airlines after Paris in Europe and also part of its rapid expansion strategy .
The Vietnamese Airlines will use Boeing 767 aircraft , every Tuesday and Thursday from Ho Chi Minh City to Frankfurt with stopovers in Hanoi and Moscow .
A spokesman of the Vietnamese Airlines said : " We initiate this route to serve lots of overseas vietnames in Germany . "
Vietname Airlines has more than 20 international destinations , many new routes were initiated last year , and earmarked further expansion .
Early this week Vietname Airlines announced the plan to double its fleet to 70 aircrafts by 2010 .
The load capacity of Vietname Airlines has grown by 1 % to 4.05 million despite the outbreak of SARS and Iraq War in 2003 .
Vietname Airlines has set 5 million as its goal for this year , about half ( 2.4 million ) of which are foreigners .
An AIDS Suffering Child Is Barred From School And The Angry Priest Principal Lodged A Lawsuit Against Officials
( AFP in Nairobi on 7th ) D 'Agostino , an outspoken American priest who is in charge of an orphanage of AIDS suffering kids in Nairobi ( capital of Kenya ) , lodged a lawsuit against the Kenya government to get justice for an AIDS suffering child , demanding it to force the public school to renounce its exclusion of HIV children .
Although the number of HIV victims is estimated to be 2.5 million in the country , AIDS and HIV are still taboo subjects in Kenya .
D 'Agostino is in charge of the Nyumbani Orphanage which houses many HIV children . He claims that many of his children are barred from primary schools . The practice of these schools is against the government policy of compulsory primary school education .
Lawyer Nanwamba of D 'Agostino said at the court presided over by Judge Koome : " Barring children , especially HIV sufferers , from public schools is inhumane and illegal and violates human rights . Receiving education is a basic human right and turning down these children is an infringement upon their rights . "
D 'Agostino is seeking a court order to force the school accept children without inquiring whether or not they are infected with HIV .
The Kenya Ministry of Education said through its lawyer Gacirih that it does not know about the discrimination but understands the practice of the school .
Gacirih said that the Education Ministry is ready to solve the problem through negotiation with Nyumbani Home for Children located on the Northwest Outskirts of Nairobi .
Koome orders the two sides to talk it over and report the result of the talk tomorrow .
US Is to Set Free Hundreds of Iraqi Prisoners
( AFP in Baghdad ) The interim Chief Executive Officer Bremer , appointed by the American Government , announces in his policy address today that the occupying coalition forces headed by US will release 100 Iraqi prisoners on 8th and hundreds will be freed in the following weeks .
Bremer , accompanied by Pachachi , Chairman of Iraq Interim Governing Council , offers a new reward for the capture of any other most wanted criminals , the highest reward being 200,000 USD .
Pachachi praises the above measure taken by the coalition , saying that this is the result of the forceful canvassing of the Governing Council .
Pachachi told journalists : " Governing Council has long been committed to advocating the reconciliation spirit among the Iraqi people . To achieve the goal , we demand the coalition forces to review the problem of prisoners . "
A spokesman of the occupying coalition who is not willing to reveal his name said later that altogether 506 prisoners will be released in the next few weeks .
Bremer said in his brief speech : " The coalition will release the first hundred prisoners . "
Bremer displays a conciliatory stance at a time when the occupying coalition is trying to pacify the resentments of Sunni Islam society under Hussein .
Hussein was captured by American troops following 8 months on the fugitive run .
Bremer said : " The tyrant Hussein is imprisoned now and most of his underlings are either killed or captured . It is the right time for reconciliation . "
The conditions for release are the prisoners " must give up violence " ; they have to find community personages , religious or clan leaders as guarantors ; The guarantors must be responsible for good and lawful behaviors of the prisoners .
Bremer points out that none of the prisoners to be set free are directly involved in violence against American troops or other deadly attacks , nor are they related to any anti-human crimes .
Bremer said that those to be freed " have come to see their crimes " and " we are ready to provide some of them opportunities to repent and start anew . "
Experts from WHO of Come to Guangzhou Again to Investigate Source of SARS
( AFP in Guangzhou on 10th ) The World Health Organization ( WHO ) has began its second investigation today into the SARS cases which cropped up again in the south of mainland China .
The WHO has already conducted study of the first proved SARS case since 6 months ago .
An expert group of the WHO and China 's public health authorities carried out a surprise inspection of a restaurant of seafood and game in Guangzhou , trying to find out the source of a proved SARS case and a suspected SARS case .
The WHO spokesman Wadia said in Guangzhou : " This action starts with the examination of the data collected last time ... We will try to integrate the fragments of information . "
At the same time the Chinese government calls on the public to kill mice and other animals that might carry SARS viruses .
The restaurant targeted by public health officials is located in the old city center in Guangzhou . It is open round the clock . A 20-year-old waitress here has been diagnosed as a suspected SARS patient Wednesday night .
Expert Robert Breiman said : " We have had a very careful examination of the possible environmental problem in the restaurant and we will do further investigation . "
He said : " We talked with the staff of the restaurant , asked about its procedure of operations and visited the cooking quarters . And the environment experts will continue the work . "
Breiman said that it is still too early to come to a conclusion about the source of the disease , for experts are to sort out their data for evaluation .
The US Openly Supports The Establishment of An International Thermonuclear Experimental Reactor in Japan
( AFP in Tokyo on 10th ) The US openly supports for the first time the establishment of " International Thermonuclear Experimental Reactor " involving an investment of billions of USD in Aomori County , Japan instead of Cadarache , France . It claims that Japan can provide a favorable location .
The plan for the ITER will choose either Cadarache in France or Rokkasho of Aomori in Japan .
The plan aims to provide an experimental site for simulating solar nuclear fusion which is eulogized as the cleanest , safest and inexhaustible source of energy in the future .
However , it is generally predicted that no electricity can be generated by this program before 2050 .
The US Energy Minister Abraham said at a gathering of business leaders when he was visiting Tokyo that " today I am honored to point out US strongly supports the establishment of ITER in Japan .
Technically speaking , you can supply advantageous site . "
Abraham said " Rokkasho of Japan 's Aomori is the right place for receiving large quantities of materials needed for the set-up of ITER . Your celebrated technology and engineering skills are admired all over the world . Besides , the communities in the locality explicitly welcome this program and wish Rokkasho of Aomori to be selected as its location . "
The spokesman of US Embassy in Tokyo confirms that this is the first time for Washington authorities to openly support Japan who is trying to have ITER located in Japan .
Official of Japan 's Ministry of Education , Culture , Sports , Science and Technology said " Abraham 's speech is really inspiring . "
We will continue our cooperation with other countries and try to have ITER established at Rokkasho of Aomori in Japan .
The Philippines Communists Refuse to Hold Peace Talks With the Arrono 's And Launch New Guerilla Activities
( AFP in Manila on 10th ) The Philippine Military says that the Communist troops have launched a new round of attacks including attacking a power plant and burning down a telecom tower , killing 8 people .
These attacks occurred at the same time when the spokesman of Communist Party of the Philippines-New People 's Army ( NPA ) was making an announcement claiming that NPA will no longer talk peace with the Philippine President Arrono and will wait until the successor comes to power .
The NPA spokesman Rosal said on TV : " We no longer cherish any hope about peace talks with Arrono even if she claims they are ready to talk . "
The Philippine government originally planned to resume initial talks later this month with the Philippine Communists about formal peace negotiation .
Rosal points out that the Philippine Communists will demand the candidates of opposition to Arrono in May election to put forward their proposals on peace talks when they are elected .
Rosal says the Philippine Communists demand to be excluded from the lists of terrorist organizations of US and Europe and set this as a precondition of peace negotiation .
50 Philippine Communist guerrillas attacked Calaca power plant and the government troops guarding the plant . 3 government soldiers and 4 Communist guerrillas were killed and 7 government soldiers wounded .
The Unemployed People Launched Protest Activities . Iraqi Police And British Troops Killed 6 Civilians .
( AFP in Baghdad on 10th ) 6 Iraqi civilians were shot and killed today by Iraqi police and British troops who opened fire at protesters in southern Iraq .
Meanwhile , after the Pentagon announced that Hussein is regarded as a war prisoner , he will probably be trialed in 6 months .
3 big blasts were heard in one hour in Baghdad this morning , but US Military claim they haven 't had any news about it .
Baghdad suffered a series of car bomb attacks these days , with the latest occurring on December 31 . A busy restaurant was blown up with 8 killed and 24 injured .
Meanwhile , the American army also launched large-scaled offensive called " Pinchers Action " , bombarding the insurgents strongholds on the outskirts of Baghdad . Roar of guns are heard all over the capital .
In another development , the coalition forces headed by US said today that an American " Black Hawk " helicopter crashed near Fallujah last week . It was probably attacked by the anti-US guerrillas .
9 people were killed in the incident .
The coalition forces say that 2 Iraqi policemen were killed by mistake by the US army in Kirkuk City where situation is tense .
Meanwhile , in the southern city of Amarah , hundreds of unemployed Iraqis launched protests . In the end the police and the British troops opened fire to disperse the crowds , 6 people killed at least and 8 injured .
China Has Sent A Delegation to US To Purchase over 2 Billion USD Worth of Hi-Tech Equipments
( AFP in Beijing on 12th ) The official media report that a Chinese purchasing delegation in US will sign several contracts to buy over 2 billion USD worth of hi-tech equipments from American manufacturers .
Beijing Morning quotes an official from the Ministry of Information Industry that these business contracts will be concluded in US tomorrow . The manufacturers include Motorola Semi-Conductor Manufacturing Company , Intel Corporation and Cisco System Corporation .
The Chinese manufacturers participating in the signing of contracts are some major telecom and computer makers including China Telecom Group and Lenovo Group Company .
This is the 3rd purchasing delegation sent to US by China since last November .
China is taking actions to reduce her growing favorable trade balance with US . The above measure is part of her endeavor .
Beijing Morning reports that an official from the American Department of Commerce welcomes this action , for it helps to reduce the deficit of American trade with China .
According to the American statistics , the American deficit of trade with China last year hit 103 billion USD . The deficit is predicted to reach 130 million USD by 2003 .
Syria Criticizes Israel for Lack of Sincerity in Its Invitation of Syrian President to Visit Israel
( AFP in Damascus on 12th ) Israeli President Katsav today invites Syrian President Al-Assad to visit Jerusalem for peace talks . The Syrian officials denounces the invitation as lack of sincerity and accuses Israel of trying to avoid the Middle East peace process of land for peace .
Katsav said on Israeli Public Radio Station early today : " I invite President Al-Assad to visit Jerusalem so that conditions of a peace accord can be talked seriously with Israeli 's leader . "
Katsav also said : " Al-Assad will be welcomed and he should not set prerequisites . "
The Syrian Minister of Overseas Syrian Nationals Al-Sharaa indicates when interviewed by the American Cable News Network ( CNN ) that Israel must explicitly express its willingness to resume the talk from where the negotiation broke off 4 years ago .
Al-Sharaa points out that the invitation sent by Katsav is not " a sincere response " to President Al-Assad who appealed last month to Israel to resume contact . He accuses Katsav of trying to get the lime-light .
The Syrian official news agency SANA quotes a nameless senior official who accuses Israel of trying to avoid the Middle East peace process based on land for peace .
This official said that " it is not a question of visiting or taking the initiative ; the purpose of recent Israeli speeches is to avoid peace process . "
This official also states : " Any plan or measure for partial settlement cannot bring peace to the Middle East . "
When talking with Al-Assad 's late father King Al-Assad Senior , the then Israeli premier Barak agreed to withdraw from almost all Golan Heights and to keep only the east coast of Sea of Galiaee as a narrow corridor .
However , the Damascus authorities refuses to accept the proposal and wishes Israel to return all the land on Golan Heights which was occupied by Israel in 1976 War and annexed in 1981 .
Rifts within The Commanding System of The Largest Rebellious Group in Liberia Are Deepened
( AFP in Monrovia on 12th ) After the Leader of " LURD " Conneh was expelled , power struggle within this largest rebellious army group is growing tense . A leader of the rebellious army insists that Conneh still maintain the power .
LURD rose up in 1999 to fight against the former president Taylor and kindled the 4-year-long civil war in Liberia . Now it occupies about 4 fifths of Liberia .
In mid-August last year Taylor agreed to exile to Nigeria so as to pave way for peace agreement in this western African country . The former government , the rebellious army and the out-parties formed an interim government .
But a group which calls itself " High Military Command " of LURD accuses Conneh of selling the post of LURD in the transitional government to fill his own pocket . Some time ago it adopted Aisha Keita Conneh , the divorced wife of Conneh , as the new leader .
But Dweh , parliament speaker of the transitional government and founder of LURD , insists that only the national executive committee of LURD has the right to recall the leader of the organization .
He told the media the night before last : " I founded LURD in Nigeria ; I can guarantee to the Liberian people that there is no rift within LURD and nothing can sabotage the peace process . "
Dweh attributes the internal strife to the behind-the-scene manipulation of the transitional government leader Bryant and other LURD leaders who serve in the transitional government .
Bryant who used to be a merchant was appointed last October as the leader of this war-ridden country until 2005 general election .
Dweh accuses the ministers of justice , communications and labor of colluding with Aisha Conneh , supported by Bryant , promising her that she would be the LUDR leader as soon as Conneh is out of power .
He warns that , if Bryant continues to violate the peace accord , the warring parties will return to Accra where the accord was prepared and discuss whether Bryant should be replaced .
Former US Boxer Charges A Boxing Advertising Company with Bribing Him to Purposely Loose in The Match
( AFP in New York on 12th ) According to New York Daily News , the former US boxer Rose says that Top Rank Company , US Professional Boxing Promoter , provides 5,000 USD as bribery to make him deliberately loose in the game .
Top Rank Company run by Arum is now being investigated by the US Federal Bureau of Investigation .
The 34-year-old Rose says that , several weeks before his match with another American boxer Esch nicknamed Butterbean in December 1995 , two representatives of Top Rank Company called at his house .
Rose told the newspaper : " Soon after mid-day when I was having a rest at home , somebody knocked on the door . Through the peeping hole I saw two white employees of Top Rank . They wanted to talk about my boxing match with Butterbean . "
" They said : We have brought some money for you , a large sum . They wanted me to lose and not to defeat Butterbean . "
Rose told the 1995 incident to the investigators ; the case is part of the 20-month-long investigation into embezzlements in the boxing fields .
Rose turned down the bribery and knocked down the ever-victorious Esch in the second round of the match on Madison Square Garden .
New York Daily News went to the residence of Esch in Alabama and asked whether or not he believed what Rose said . Esch defended Top Rank , saying : " Rose is no match in strength . How is it possible for you to ask a boxer to purposely lose when his record is 1 win and 6 defeats ? I don 't think Top Rank violates the law . "
FBI went to Las Vegas on 6th to inspect the headquarters of Top Rank and confiscated some of its financial and medical documents and computers .
It is reported that FBI is collecting evidences about pre-game decision of results including the September championship match between Mosley and Hoya .
US Wishes Asian Countries to Get Rid of The Fear for Mad Cow Disease
( AFP in Manila on 14th ) Officials of the American Department of Agriculture indicate that Asian countries can soon eat American beef without fear although a mad cow disease case cropped up last month .
After the first mad cow disease case was identified in America , its quarantine was strengthened immediately . Despite this , Japan , South Korea and a few other Asian countries soon prohibited or limited their import of American beef at once .
American officials said yesterday that the related departments have expanded their investigation of MCD . Beef from the place where the case was identified was not exported . Besides , for nearly a decade the related departments have kept strengthening their quarantine to prevent the eruption of mad cow disease .
Mad cow disease is also called Bovine Spongiform Encephalopathy ( BSE ) and it is related to human brain spongy pathology Creutzfeldt-Jakob Disease ( CJD ) that leads to cavitation of human brain .
Greene , the US agriculture department director for Asia said at a press conference : " We are optimistic that Asian countries will further reduce their prohibition in about a month . "
Greene also said : " We have assured all Asian countries about the safety of American beef . "
He said that the Japanese delegation was visiting the USA to study the measures taken to prevent the mad cow disease .
South Korea Intensifies Its Quarantine to Prevent Spread of The Bird Flu
( AFP in Seoul on 14th ) South Korean officials say that new bird flu cases appear after 9 peaceful days . South Korea has intensified its quarantine to prevent spread of the bird flu .
South Korean Ministry of Agriculture says that an intensive quarantine zone has been set up near a chicken farm in Yangsan district 390 km southeast of Seoul .
The officials from Ministry of Public Health detected bird flu virus in this region on Monday .
This is the first time for South Korea to find bird flu virus in 9 days .
Last month bird flu popped up in 15 regions in South Korea and the authorities was compelled to kill nearly two million chickens and ducks . The devastating infectious disease in obviously is under control .
Head of the Animal Health Division under South Korean Public Health Ministry Kim Chang-Seob said : " we kill all the poultry in the infected regions and no poultry is allowed to move . "
The appearance of new bird flue cases forces South Korean government officials to intensify quarantine in other regions .
Kim Chang-Seob says that this kind of virus can survive in dust for 2 weeks and in the poultry excrement and urine for 35 days at least .
At The Summit of American States , Bush Managed with Difficulty to Save The Plan for A Free Trade Area
( AFP in Monterrey on 13th ) The US president Bush has been trying to carry out his ambitious plan for a free trade area in Americas . Today at the summit of American States he won the support of 33 state leaders .
But the countries which attend the summit hold different ideas about poverty in the western hemisphere which is growing more and more serious . The US has failed to include his anti-corruption clause into the final communique .
The Free trade Area of the Americas starts from Alaska in the north to Argentina in the south . It is claimed to be the largest free area in the world with a population of 800 million and a total output value of 1,300 billion USD .
However , the Argentine President Kirchner attacked the US plan at the closing ceremony of the 2-day summit . In his speech he said that the problems in Americas cannot be solved by merely establishing a free trade area .
The largest economy in South America - Brazil and the major gasoline supplier for US - Venezuela are both opposed to including the subject of the Free Trade Area of the Americas into the meeting 's agenda . After heated discussions the state leaders finally agree to announce that talks over the establishment of a free trade area will be completed by January 2005 .
Political Strife in Iran Is Getting Increasingly Fierce And The Reformists Threaten to Resign
( AFP in Tehran on 13th ) Struggle has erupted between Iranian reformists and powerful conservatives over the candidate qualification for election . Today things are getting worse and several cabinet leaders threaten to resign unless conservatives make concessions on keeping reformist candidates from participating in election .
One of the Vice-Presidents Sattarifar warns that the whole government may resign if the attempt of the Guardian Council to disqualify thousands of candidates for the parliament election on February 20 is not prevented .
Sattarifar said : " If the government cannot fulfil its duty of protecting people 's rights and holding free election , it will not be the option to continue the administration . "
Governors of 27 provinces in Iran also threaten to resign together . Persons near President Khatami reveal that at least 10 ministers have prepared their resignations .
However , some media indicates that President Khatami with a gentle disposition also asks to resign . This is denied by Khatami 's assistant .
The angry reformist parliament members are holding their sit-in protest in the parliament building for the 3rd day and say they are ready to continue the sit-in demonstration for weeks .
83 of the reformist parliament members are disqualified so that they cannot participate in election for a second term .
Iranian News Agency ( IRNA ) says the parliament members have challenged the Guardian Council and demands it to withdraw its decision of disqualifications .
The Guardian Council made up of 12 members is not elected by people and is a stronghold for anti-reform right wing forces .
Nobel peace laureate Ms. Ebadi who has been hated by hard liners says she will visit the parliament to show her support to the sit-in demonstration of the reformist parliament members .
The Appreciation of New Zealand Dollar Does Not Affect The Confidence of Entrepreneurs in New Zealand
( AFP in Wellington on 15th ) According to the latest quarterly survey released by New Zealand Institute of Economic Research , people in the business world still have confidence in New Zealand despite the soaring New Zealand dollar .
The report points out that enterprises pessimistic about the enterprise environment in the next 6 months account for only 2 % . By contrast the figures in the last 2 seasons were 3 % and 20 % respectively .
The above-mentioned Institute points out that the indexes in the report show a steady economic growth in the 4th season of last year . The activities of the enterprise field have increased by 31 % .
However , according to the foreseeable goals the economic growth of New Zealand is predicted " to further slide down gradually in the following seasons . "
Gardiner , economist with New Zealand Institute of Economic Research , says that New Zealand dollar has been appreciated fast in the past 3 months , which results in widening of confidence difference between exporters and non-exporters .
Predicably , 11 % of manufacturing and building exporters will have less promising prospects in the next 6 months and 40 % of non-exporters feel optimistic about the enterprises ' prospects in the next 6 months .
The New Zealand dollar has appreciated 30 percent over the past two years .
The Resignation of Chief Financier And North America Director of Adecco Has Caused Doubts Outside This Broker Company
( AFP in Zurich on 16th ) Chief Financial Officer and North America Director of Adecco ( world 's largest manpower broker for temporary employment Weber has resigned after the company 's accounting problems were reported . This has caused the outsiders to fear that another enterprise scandal will be staged .
It is not until this week that Weber plays down the delay of Adecco in publishing its annual statements . The statements should have been made public on February 4 , but the publishing was delay because major weaknesses of internal control in the business of its North America Manpower Company were found .
Weber 's post will be replaced by Chief Accountant Cano for the time being .
Chief executive officer Arrieta of Adecco has also resigned and he will be succeeded by Marcel , Chairman of Adecco France , largest one-country company of Adecco Group in the overseas .
Besides , the former Chairman Bowmer became the consultative president after he left office . Now he will resume the actual management and take over the company in crises and the current Group CEO Caille " focus his attention on daily affairs . "
Traders say that the top personnel change of Adecco once again puts the company under pressure to sell .
At 40 minutes past 9 , Adecco shares dropped by 3.6 % , becoming a little stable after the big drop at the opening quotation . On the Swiss stock market at the same time the big quotation stood at a 20.3 rise .
Adecco 's shares fell into a turmoil after it announced on Monday that the publishing of its annual financial statements would be postponed .
Japan Decides to Strike Budget Balance within 10 Years
( AFP in Tokyo on 16th ) Japan 's Finance Minister Sadakazu Tanigaki said today that he is fully confident that the world 's second largest economy will get rid of a " financial crisis " and the finance will be rectified within 10 years .
Sadakazu Tanigaki says the total deficit of the central and local governments has reached 5 % of Japan 's GDP . If an average of 0.5 % could be reduced each year , the deficit would be removed in 10 years .
He told a group of journalists : " Japan 's financial situation is still in crisis .
We are the worst among major industrial countries in terms of ( financial ) circulation and reserves . "
Japan decides to turn " original deficit " into " original surplus " by March 2014 --- It will be a multi-level financial balance for the first time in over 2 decades .
This is the first time for the administration headed by Prime Minister Junichiro Koizumi to put forward a clear goal for Japan to get " original surplus " again . In this circumstance , tax transcendence does not include the expenditures for paying back debts .
The last such surplus occurred in the year before March 1992 . The 6-year-long surplus ended thence .
Tokyo Stock Exchange Has Approved The Application of Shinsei Bank for Listing
( AFP in Tokyo on 16th ) Tokyo Stock Exchange says today that it has ratified the application of Shinsei Bank for listing . The trade of shares of Shinsei Bank will start on February 19 .
Shinsei Bank , taken over and reshaped by the American Investment Fund - Ripplewood Holding , will , for the first time , issue 242 million shares for the domestic investors in Japan and 188 million shares for overseas investors .
The price for the first open issuing will be determined on February 9 .
Shinsei Bank has also prepared 36.3 million shares for possible excess purchase , for possibly some subscriptions might not be realized .
The predecessor of Shinsei Bank was Long-Term Credit Bank of Japan Ltd. which became state-owned after bankruptcy in 1998 . The reshaped Shinsei Bank already offers retail financial service .
The net profit of Shinsei Bank in the year by the end of March 2003 is expected to hit 65 billion Japanese Yen ( 613 million USD ) , a 22.6 % growth over the previous year . Its ordinary profit is 60 billion Japanese Yen , a 76.5 % growth ; its total business income is 175 billion Japanese Yen , a 13 % decline .
Shinsei Bank also indicates that its total bad obligation was 132.3 billion Japanese Yen , less than 154.2 billion 3 months ago .
The Death Toll of The Bam Earthquake in Iran Rose to 41,000
( AFP in Tehran on 16th ) The spokesman of Iranian supreme religious leader Khamenei says that the earthquake which hit the ancient city of Bam of Iran on December 26 last year has killed 41,000 people . The final death toll could be as high as 45,000 .
But the original estimation of death was about 30,000 to 35,000 .
Dean Mohammadi-Gholpayghani of Khamenei office told Iran State News Agency ( IRNA ) : " So far the number of people killed in the Bam earthquake has reached 41,000 and the final death toll could be 45,000 . "
Iran News Agency quotes him : " This is a tragic disaster . "
He pledges at the same time that the government will speed up the reconstruction .
The number of injuries in the Bam earthquake is about 30,000 .
A senior provincial official says that it will take 2 years to reconstruct Bam City . Currently the government has started to invite Iranian and foreign bidders for the reconstruction .
Thousands of Anti-Nuclear Protesters March in Paris
( AFP in Paris on 17th ) Up to 15,000 anti-nuclear protestors marched in Paris against a new generation of reactors , accusing police of stirring trouble by allowing a separate rally against a ban on religious headscarves in schools .
The main target of the anti-nuclear protests is the European Pressurized Water Reactor ( EPWR ) , the first of which is to be built in Finland by a consortium including the French state-owned Areva group and German engineering giant Siemens at a cost of three billion euros ( 3.7 billion US dollars ) .
France , which is one of the most nuclear energy-dependent countries in the world , is expected to give the reactors the green light in the near future to begin replacing some of the 58 plants that produce 80 percent of the country 's electricity and are nearing the end of service .
" It is in fact a veritable revival of nuclear energy which is unfolding before us , " said Lhomme , a spokesman for the group End Nuclear Network which organized the demonstration .
Lhomme criticized the police for allowing another gathering . He said : " We are convinced that the interior ministry is looking for trouble . "
The interior ministry oversees police in French cities .
Nearly at the same time and in the same place in Paris another gathering took place which attracted thousands of people to take part in protest of a government plan to prohibit wearing turbans and other " clear " religious symbols in schools .
The demonstrators , who numbered more than 15,000 according to organizers and under 6,000 according to police , built a pyramid of tin cans in the square denouncing what they called the " radioactive waste scandal left for future generations " .
Baghdad : 23 People Killed and 95 Injured in a Suicidal Bomb
( AFP in Baghdad on 18th ) According to the US troops and the Iraqi Hospital , in the suicidal car bomb that destroyed the gate of the US Army Headquarters in Baghdad the death toll has added up to 23 and the injuries are up to 95 .
Doctor Muhammad Gumar of Karama Teaching Hospital said : " We have accepted 3 bodies and 30 injuried people . "
The latest casualty report adds 3 persons to the death toll .
The US Army spokesman said earlier that the US army hospital reported 18 killed and 28 injured ; of the dead , 16 were Iraqi civilians and two were American employees of the US Department of Defence .
Besides , a first-aid doctor points out that in Al-Yarmook Hospital of Baghdad two persons show no response to treatment .
Other local hospitals report no death , but Al-Yarmook , Al-Khindi and Neurosurgery Hospitals report a total of 37 injuries .
The afore-mentioned spokesman confirms that the injuries under treatment in US Army Hospital are 22 Iraqi civilians , 4 American contractors and 2 US soldiers .
So far it is not known whether or not the death toll includes the person who carried out the suicidal attack .
Shrinking Workforce to Knock Economic Output in EU , Japan
( AFP in Davos , Switzerland on 19th ) The European Union 's share of global economic output is reduced almost half by 2050 as its workforce shrinks , according to a study report published today by the World Economic Forum ( WEF ) and US consultancy firm Watson Wyatt Worldwide .
By contrast the plenty of labor in such developing countries such as India and China should help to promote economic growth .
Sammans , a managing director at the WEF , said " Economic output is determined by labour force growth and productivity rates , "
In countries where labor force is in serious short supply , commodities and labor supply probably cannot meet the needs and living standards . "
A report entitled " Living happier ever after : the economic implications of aging societies " points out that because of the prolonging of people 's lives due to medical progress , the retirees , in relation to labor force , will continue to increase ( especially in the developed countries ) , which finally will exercise immediate impact on economic production .
A statement in response to the research report points out that " Suppose the current vital statistics and economic trends keep unchanged . By 2050 the proportion of EU in the world economic output value will be reduced from the present 18 % to 10 % . "
The statement also warns " that the proportion of Japan will shrink from 8 % to 4 % . "
The Damage of Artistic Works by The Israeli Ambassador in Sweden Gave Rise to The Diplomatic Dispute between The Two Countries .
( AFP in Stockholm on 18th ) A work of art in memory of a Palestinian suicidal bomb attacker in the Swedish History Museum was damaged by the Israeli ambassador Mazel in Sweden . It has given rise to a dispute which has developed into a diplomatic strife due to the intervention by Israeli Prime Minister Sharon .
Ambassador Mazel visited Stockholm Museum last Friday when he saw a work of art on show which portrays a suicidal attacker in Haifa in October last year . He deliberately damaged it , for which he expelled by the museum authority . This has led to a diplomatic conflict between Israel and Sweden .
Israel demands that Sweden remove this exhibit , which was turned down by Sweden .
The event has been extensively covered by Swedish press .
The exhibition is part of an international Conference sponsored by the Swedish government on racial massacre . Israel will also attend the conference .
The on-the-spot video-tape shows the Israeli ambassador tearing down the spotlight of the conference hall and throwing it into water , resulting in the short circuit of the artistic work . Afterwards , the museum president ordered that Ambassador Mazel leave the museum .
Today Israeli Prime Minister Sharon supported Mazel , which resulted the event developed into an all-round diplomatic dispute .
The work of art on display is chiefly a ship named " White Snow " sailing on sea . On the stem is a picture of smiling Hanadi Jaradat which serves as the sail .
Hanadi was a Palestine lawyer on probation who lived in Israel and whose younger brother had been killed by an Israeli bomb . To avenge her brother she launched a suicidal bomb attack last October in the northern Israeli city of Haifa , killing 21 Israelis and causing a new round of Israel vs Palestine conflicts .
Mazel said : " I cannot bear to see this picture . It is a great hurt to the victims ' family members of Haifa bombing . As the Israeli ambassador , I cannot be aloof and indifferent about the picture which stand facts on their head . "
The Democratic Party Says That The Baghdad Bombing Case Is An Evidence of The Failure of American Policies Towards Iraq
( AFP in Washington on 18th ) The Democratic Party 's candidates who seek to replace Bush in the White House point out today one after another that the latest suicidal bomb attack which caused great casualties is an evidence showing the failure of American policies towards Iraq .
The attack killed at least 25 and injured about 30 . This is the attack that has caused greatest casualties since American occupied Iraq .
Democratic Party 's opponents of Bush attack Bush 's Iraqi policies in strong terms . Some claim that the attack is the latest evidence of the failure of Bush 's policies towards Iraq .
Senator Edwards from North Carolina told Columbia Broadcasting Corporation : " Our policies have failed . I don 't know why the government is unwilling change . "
He said : " Obviously , the first thing we should do is to internationalize the peace-keeping troops in Iraq . The other thing is to hand over the transitional administration to UN . "
The former president Carter and the Democratic Party 's candidate Dean said when they made appearance in public that the Iraqi war led by US " has proved not only that it was based on wrong information and misguided statements " , but also that the latest attack " continues to show it is a tragedy " .
Dean has regarded anti-Iraqi war as the main shaft of his running program .
Iraqi Guerillas Attack Helicopters of The US Army with Hi-Tech Weapons
( AFP in Washington on 18th ) Senior American army officers say that Iraqi insurgents attack US helicopters with increasingly precision weapons .
A group of senior officials who are familiar with a confidential report told New York Times that a confidential military report reveals Iraqi guerrillas attack US helicopters with grenades propelled by rockets and heat-seeking surface-to-air missiles .
They claim that the report had been prepared before US helicopters were attacked on 3 occasions this month . However , the recent 3 attacks further confirm the conclusion of the report .
The report aims to provide US pilots with methods of how to evade attacks by such weapons . The officials are reluctant to discuss the new contents recently discovered .
But judging from the new round of attacks in Iraq , people cannot help feeling worried that Iraqi guerrillas have carefully studied the fighting style of American aircrafts .
Researchers have found that Iraqi guerrillas have used SA-16 shoulder-fired missiles more than once , which is really worrying .
Missiles with such precision guidance systems can hardly be evaded by pilots .
A senior US pilot in the Persian Gulf said : " Every successful attack of our aircrafts is a great victory strategically for our enemy .
Not only it is covered by media but also it is a clear-cut judgement of victory or defeat . Therefore , our enemy believes it is a useful maneuver . "
Since October 25 last year , 9 US helicopters have already been downed or crashed with at least 49 US soldiers killed .
Carter Praises Dean on The Eve of Initial Election of Democratic Party in Iowa
( AFP in Plains of Georgia on 18th ) The former American President Carter praises Dean 's , candidate for election and former Vermont Governor , " courageous and outspoken " opposition to the Iraq war on the eve of the first time initial election of President candidate in Democratic Party in Iowa .
Carter told journalists in his hometown , Plains of Georgia : " I have been very grateful to Governor Dean for his courageous and outspoken stance and position from the outset . "
This Nobel peace laureate said : " For the past one and a half years I have devoted much time on opposing this completely unnecessary and unjust Iraqi War .
