Carter calls Dean a powerful " champion for peace " . Although he did not give endorsement to his statement , American TV stations all report his speech .
As left-wing former governor of a northern state Dean may be at a disadvantage in Southern states when confronting the retired general Clark , a middle-of-the-roader from Arkansas . But Carter 's support may increase his chance of victory in southern states whose positions are conservative and which are more religious .
Carter said recently in a TV interview that he believes that Dean is the most likely candidate in Democratic Party to oppose to Bush .
The Democratic Party Criticizes Bush for Creating The New Axis of Evil
( AFP in Washington on 21st ) The American Democratic Party not in office accuses Bush for leading US into isolation in the world and criticizes him for creating the new " axis of evil " .
The Democratic leader at the House of Representatives Pelosi attacked , when the Democratic Party was rebroadcasting the President 's State of the Union Policy speech , the President for the casualties and expenses resulting from sending troops to Iraq .
Because it is the year of American presidential election looms ( to be held on November 2 this year ) , the Democratic Party has prepared heavy bombs for Bush .
Clark , one of the persons struggling for Democratic nomination , says that Bush had worked out his own " axis of evil " .
Bush used the term of " axis of evil " in his State of the Union Policy speech 2 years ago to refer to those countries which pose as threat to the US .
Clark said : " That is an axis of an accounting policy that menaces our future , a diplomatic policy that threatens our security and a domestic policy that puts our families to death . "
US Appeals to Iran Authorities to Allow A Free And Fair Parliament Election Once Again
( AFP in Washington on 21st ) The political crisis resulting from the conflict between Iranian conservatives and reformers over the qualification of candidates for parliament election has continued . US appeals to Iran once again that the election to be held in February be free and fair .
Deputy spokesman Ereli of the State Department said : " We hold that it is important for Iranian leaders to permit a free and fair election in accordance with internationally accepted procedures . The Iranian government should respond to people 's demand . "
Ereli points out : " The political situation in Iran is changing and there are many developments every day . We keep a close watch of the situation there . "
Ereli made the above remarks when asked by journalists about the resignation of cabinet ministers and deputy president of Iranian government .
It is reported that some cabinet ministers and the deputy president in the reformist government led by Iranian President Khatami apply to resign in protest of disqualification of large numbers of reformist candidates for the parliament election to be held on 20th next month .
Japan : A Small Plane Crashed in A Residential area And 3 on board Killed
( AFP in Tokyo on 22nd ) Today a small aeroplane crashed into a residential area in Yamanashi Prefecture . 3 people on board were killed . Luckily , the nearby houses , a kindergarten and a hospital " miraculously " survived the disaster .
The Yamanashi Prefecture government official Yamamoto in charge of emergency said that the Cessna 172p mono-engine plane piloted by a 32-year-old youth crashed on a small parking lot .
One of the victims was a photographer who was taking picture of the children outside the kindergarten who were lining up for forming words .
The kindergarten in question is only 100 meters from the site of the plane crash .
Yamamoto said : " The small plane crashed beside several houses and a hospital and 3 people on board were all killed .
It is a real miracle that the plane did not hit any house or the hospital .
At that time the wind was high and the engine oil was leaking . If the plane fell on a house or the hospital ,
it would inevitably cause fire . "
An aviation official from Transport Ministry said that the plane took off from the Chofu Airport in the west of Tokyo this morning and was scheduled to return in 2 hours .
The cause of the accident is still unknown .
NASA Said There Is Now No News from The Spirit Mars Probe
( AFP in Washington on 22nd ) An official from NASA said today that NASA has lost contact with Spirit , a Mars probe that has landed on Mars , due to serious faults .
Mars Exploration Rover Project Manager Theisinger said : " We have found serious abnormalities with the Probe . "
NASA said yesterday that thundering and lightning over Australia made it impossible for scientists to send daily instructions to Spirit .
But some experts believe that the suspension of communication was caused by more serious problems .
Spirit landed on Mars on January 3 and began to look for signs of life that might have existed on this red star last week .
The twin probing vehicle Opportunity of Spirit is expected to touch down at night from January 24 to 25 .
This probing mission costs 820 million USD . It was planned that the 2 solar energy probes would operate for 3 months .
US Feels Optimistic about Resuming Talks with North Korea after Discussing with Japan And South Korea
( AFP in Washington on 22nd ) US said today that it feels " very optimistic " about resuming the multi-nation negotiation to end up the nuclear deadlock in North Korea . But the US also said that only a little progress has been made in urging Pyongyang to come back to the negotiation table .
Kelly , the top US diplomat for the East Asia and Pacific Affair , said : " We believe it is very likely that the 6-party talk will be resumed . But we havn 't have a clear time table yet . "
Kelly had a discussion with Japanese and South Korean senior officials about the nuclear developments in North Korea . He said that the likelihood to hold the 2nd round of talks is great . We will finally make North Korea give up its nuclear program .
Kelly told journalists : " We believe the likelihood to resume the 6-party talk is great . "
But he said that the agreement to be reached should be comprehensive and inclusive and should include the guarantee of Pyongyang to accept inspection so as to completely abolish the enriched uranium and plutonium plan and the existing nuclear weapons .
North Korea once showed what they called plutonium to the unofficial representatives of US but denied having any uranium enrichment program . It also refuted the American allegation that North Korea acknowledged , during the 2002 talk , having an uranium enrichment program .
The World Health Organization Confirms The 6th Death Case from The Bird Flu in Vietnam
( AFP in Hanoi on 24th ) The World Health Organization ( WHO ) confirms today the 6th bird flu death case in Vietnam . A 13-year-old boy in the southern of Vietname , Ho Chin Minh City died from infection of bird flu virus .
This is the first confirmed case of death from bird flu in southern Vietnam .
The Vietnamese health officials announced earlier that the 6th bird flu case has died after treated . So far at least up to 6 people have died of the infection . People are worried about the spread of the virus to human beings .
The boy was confirmed to be infected by the virus and his test of H5N1 virus of bird flu was positive before his death .
Director of the Ho Chi Minh City Nguyen The Dung told the AFP that the boy died No. 2 Paediatric Hospital of Ho Chi Minh City on January 22 .
He was hospitalized on 19th for he was suffering from respiratory tract symptoms .
WHO says that it keeps a close watch of the development of the epidemic together with the Vietnamese authorities .
Another Vietnamese health official points out that in another hospital of Hanoi two sisters died from respiratory diseases on 22th . The health authorities suspect that they are also victims of bird flu too .
Bird Flu Erupted in Indonesia And Millions of Poultry Killed
( AFP in Djakarta on 25th ) The Indonesian Ministry of Agriculture announces today that millions of chickens have died from bird flu . But no case of human infection has been reported so far .
Director of Animal Department under Ministry of Agriculture Sudardjat told the public not to feel panic . In Indonesia no human being has been infected by this possible deadly disease .
In Asia 7 countries have reported bird flu epidemic and 6 people have died in Vietnam after treatment .
The Indonesian officials pointed out earlier that the bird flu in November last year which victimized poultry on Java and Bali Islands was Newcastle disease .
The Ministry of Agriculture spokesman Priyono said this morning that there is no sign of bird flu epidemic in Indonesia so far .
He told AFP in the evening that it was not certain whether the epidemic was caused by H5N1 virus .
Most of the deaths from bird flu in Vietnam were infected by H5N1 virus .
The spokesman said that the Newcastle Disease and A-type bird flu have resulted in the death of 4.7 million poultry since November last year .
60 % of the deaths are due to Newcastle Disease .
He said that no order has been issued for the mass killing of poultry .
The Indonesia 's National News Agency quotes Sudardjat that the authorities has used British and Australian blood serum to determine the category of viruses . But the test results cannot be available until Wednesday or Thursday . By then the government will submit reports to the relevant international organizations .
Heavy Snow in Northwest Europe Caused Communication And Transport Chaos
